=================================================================================
                        RECOMMENDATIONS
=================================================================================

1. SERDES RX timing is marginal (1.044ns slack)
   Action: Verify PCB trace routing < 1cm length
           Check differential impedance (100Ω ±10%)
           Validate termination on RX side

2. PLL stability at 2.5 GHz
   Action: Place decoupling caps within 5mm of PLL power pins
           Use star grounding for reference clock
           Separate analog and digital ground planes

3. High power dissipation (156.7 mW)
   Action: Ensure adequate thermal via area under device
           Verify PCB thermal design for -40 to +85C range
           Monitor temperature at operating frequency

4. Future expansion available
   Recommendation: Can add more SERDES lanes (6 unused)
                  Can add logic up to 92.7% utilization
                  Can instantiate DSP blocks if needed


=================================================================================
                        CRITICAL DESIGN NOTES
=================================================================================

SERDES Operation:
  - 2.5 Gbps link requires careful PCB design
  - Differential pair length matching: <5mils
  - Via field around differential pairs: 5mm minimum
  - Reference clock stability: critical for PLL lock

Timing Closure:
  - High-speed design at speed grade limit
  - RX deserialization path: 1.044 ns slack (marginal)
  - Consider lower clock speed (200MHz) for better margin

Power Management:
  - Total 156.7 mW dominated by SERDES operation
  - 138.1 mW dynamic power in TX/RX paths
  - Junction temperature 67.2°C at 25°C ambient


